Nicaragua Solidarity Coalition Newsletter, April 3rd 2023

Enviado por tortilla el Sáb, 08/04/2023 - 05:08

Nicaragua Solidarity Coalition Newsletter
April 3, 2023

1. US-UN Human Rights Council campaign against Nicaragua
 
 
 
Sign on to the statement: UN Human Rights Report on Nicaragua is Fatally Flawed and Should be Withdrawn  (initial signers here) We are asking for organizations and individual to sign on to the statement to be sent to the UNHRC in protest against the dishonest and politically biased report.
 
Sign on to the statement: UN Human Rights Report on Nicaragua is Fatally Flawed and Should be Withdrawn  (initial signers here) We are asking for organizations and individual to sign on to the statement to be sent to the UNHRC in protest against the dishonest and politically biased report.
 
The Grayzone: Bad faith UN report on Nicaragua whitewashes violent US-backed coup A new, anonymously-produced UN report denouncing Nicaragua’s government whitewashes the brutal US-backed 2018 coup against it while refusing to interview victims of sadistic opposition violence. Practically the entire UN human rights system is consistently abused to supply pretexts for US economic and even military aggression against one country after another. That system depends substantially on reporting by partisan Western government and corporate funded nongovernmental organizations, abusing their nonprofit status to serve as political opposition to their respective governments, often in support of opposition violence and terrorism.
 

2. Events

April 27: Labour Friends of Latin America: End Sanctions on Venezuela; US Out of Latin America

April 28-29: Burying 200 Years of the Monroe Doctrine

3. Delegations to Nicaragua

The best way to understand the political situation in Nicaragua – and to enjoy the warmth of the people and the beauty of the country – is to join one of these delegations:

April 27-May 6 Nicaragua delegation by Friends of the ATC The delegation will visit and work with members of the Rural Workers’ Association (ATC), the organization that represents the people who grow the country’s food, a founding member of the international movement for food sovereignty, La Via Campesina.

May 13-22 Health and Hope delegation Casa Ben Linder Learn about the family and community  based health system, visit state-of-the-art hospitals and talk with policy-makers, accompany community health workers on home visits to see how integral care is provided at the grassroots level.

June 19-26 delegation: Voltage and Volcano Brigade Casa Ben Linder Visit a geothermal plant, solar installation, biogas, and electrical grid and recharging station projects. Peer into the second-most dangerous volcano in the world. Zip line among the trees of a dormant giant 

June 17-27 Nicaraguan Caribbean Coast Delegation with Friends of the ATC will visit afro-descendant and indigenous communities that are important groups in the Caribbean Coast autonomy process and Nicaraguan culture, and witness examples of concrete gains in quality of life in education, healthcare and women’s rights.
